Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.43,0:00:18.40,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:36.79,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:47.92,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.17,0:00:56.85,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.74,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:26.47,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.68,0:00:29.86,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.11,0:00:36.79,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.07,0:00:47.92,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.17,0:00:56.85,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.13,0:01:08.74,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.02,0:01:20.63,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.91,0:01:26.47,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:36.27,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.54,0:01:47.37,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(100,110)}Ep. 10 - The City of Greenery
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.19,0:01:58.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, can't you put more spring in your walking?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.68,0:01:59.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.60,0:02:01.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just what?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.09,0:02:04.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My legs are starting to hurt already.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.22,0:02:04.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.40,0:02:06.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.64,0:02:08.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.93,0:02:12.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We've not had any rest ever since we set out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.02,0:02:13.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to make a stop here?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.92,0:02:17.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No. I think I can handle a little bit more of walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.99,0:02:20.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Then, let's walk a bit slower.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.45,0:02:21.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.59,0:02:22.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.45,0:02:25.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We've not been going down the wrong road, have we?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.41,0:02:26.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.49,0:02:33.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't scare me like that. \NWe're fine, Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.67,0:02:37.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, tracks from the cart \Nthat passed through here recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.41,0:02:41.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! What a pretty bird!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.85,0:02:53.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The three of us had already walked a long way ahead \Nof dad and mom on our way to Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.41,0:03:01.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right! Walk straight, you slacker!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.92,0:03:03.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.48,0:03:08.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bard, there's no need to be that harsh with the ox... {/it's fine if you don't hit it that much}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.37,0:03:12.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing. Unless you whip this fella \Nthat much, he'll never even budge!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.48,0:03:14.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But the cart is really heavy. {/things}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.10,0:03:19.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Madam, if you show that much sympathy for an ox, \Nyou won't make it to Adelaide in this life!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.09,0:03:20.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Move it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.95,0:03:46.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They're returning to England.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.37,0:03:51.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As for us, it appears, \Nwe're not destined to see England ever again. {/return to}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.17,0:03:56.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If things don't go too well in Australia, \Nwe'll have no choice, but to return to England, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.67,0:03:59.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not going back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.79,0:04:01.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you saying that, Mr. Parker?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.91,0:04:05.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just me. \NI'm sure it's the same for your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.51,0:04:07.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.37,0:04:08.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.68,0:04:12.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After spending several months \Njust getting to this southern edge of the globe,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.54,0:04:15.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,this must be the place \Nwhere our bones will bleach. {to make (somewhere) one's final home; to make (a place) one's final resting place​ - lit: he is where we intend to bury our bones}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.24,0:04:21.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone of us knows, if you hope to carve out a new life for yourself, you have no choice but to work hard. {/fate}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.74,0:04:27.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My dad came to Australia, hoping to own a farm \Nway bigger than what he had up until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.24,0:04:29.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it seems, things won't be that easy for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.47,0:04:33.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh. Things don't seem \Nto ever go according to plan here
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.12,0:04:36.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know. It became clear enough to me, \Nwhen me and dad went to Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.58,0:04:40.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Like, for one, there's no way \Nyou can call Adelaide a proper city yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.23,0:04:45.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just some fields and woods, also roads \Nunder construction, but only a handful of houses.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.89,0:04:48.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,However, it'll grow into a big city one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.39,0:04:52.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It has all the land you could wish for, \Nso a large-scale agricultural activity is bound to begin. {/as much land as it may need} {tbh unsure what he means: 規模の大きい農業だって始まる}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.99,0:04:55.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope it comes true sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.59,0:04:57.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it definitely will.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.60,0:05:00.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I think of it, Ben, \Nwho do you intend to become in the future?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.58,0:05:04.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you plan to follow in dad's footsteps \Nand pursue agriculture?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.34,0:05:04.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.97,0:05:07.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Then, you don't want to become a farmer?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.63,0:05:08.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.88,0:05:10.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You've a dislike for farming?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.95,0:05:12.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what I meant. It's just...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.44,0:05:16.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's something I've been \Nwanting to become since long ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.29,0:05:19.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? What it is you've been \Nwanting to become, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.24,0:05:20.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.59,0:05:21.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.94,0:05:23.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.40,0:05:24.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Embarrassing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.09,0:05:28.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, if dad finds out, \Nhe would probably be terribly disappointed. {to be disappointed; to be dejected; to be downhearted; to be discouraged; to be disheartened; to lose heart; to feel let down}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.30,0:05:31.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, he'll definitely flip out right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.59,0:05:34.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm getting more curious by the second.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.49,0:05:37.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want to be, Ben?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.00,0:05:40.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I want to become a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.41,0:05:42.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? A doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.60,0:05:44.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's what I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.63,0:05:46.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I can understand the drive...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.48,0:05:50.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But this place doesn't have a single institution \Nfor you to study medicine at...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.91,0:05:54.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind that, there are no schools yet, even!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.10,0:05:55.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.12,0:05:58.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way for me \Nto become a doctor if I stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.00,0:06:16.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doing it with a cart like that... \NI bet, they can't transport a lot of stuff at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.73,0:06:19.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They do what they can, \Nwith oxen and horses being so sparse here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.60,0:06:21.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That, I already know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.35,0:06:27.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wish we'd have managed to scout a second cart, \Nso that Ben didn't have to stay behind with our things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.07,0:06:29.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell hired two, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.53,0:06:32.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's only because he's got money to burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.37,0:06:34.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's good to have money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.70,0:06:36.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to say things so obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.98,0:06:41.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't stop wondering why...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.20,0:06:42.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.88,0:06:48.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why would someone rich and prosperous would go \Nto all the trouble of coming to Southern Australia?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.88,0:06:50.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Like Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.28,0:06:55.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good question. Had he stayed in England, \Nhe'd have enjoyed a carefree life until end of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.11,0:06:58.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know! He must have done \Nsomething bad back home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.65,0:07:01.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And through that, \Nhe is no longer welcome in England.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.40,0:07:03.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May! You'd better stop with that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.65,0:07:05.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can't be saying such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.45,0:07:07.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.87,0:07:21.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Grr! I can't take this anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.54,0:07:26.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm unbelievably mad at myself \Nfor paying such good money to hire an ox that lousy! {もうわしは我慢できない 高い金を払ってこんな情けない牛を雇ったなんて自分に腹が立つ}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.45,0:07:28.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's about time the master \Nstops with the snide remarks. {using 3rd person and with "the" to reflect his disrestpectful tone} {だんなも嫌みを言い続けだね}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.47,0:07:31.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,More! More!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.30,0:07:35.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No point doing any more than that, Mr. Pettywell.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.68,0:07:37.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, lemme hold that for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.95,0:07:38.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let you hold what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.97,0:07:40.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That whip!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.09,0:07:41.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.11,0:07:43.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Go! Go faster than that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.69,0:07:46.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up! Go faster, you! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.27,0:07:50.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And you rascals walk faster, too! \NGet this! And this! And this!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.84,0:07:52.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why, if it isn't Mr. Pettywell's party?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.84,0:07:55.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. And there's our house, \Nloaded onto their cart.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.47,0:08:00.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now that you've sold it to Mr. Pettywell, \Nyou can no longer really call it "our" house, darling.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.22,0:08:02.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I shouldn't have sold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.62,0:08:04.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You've just realized?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.63,0:08:10.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The fact I had to sell it to that sort of man \Nonly makes me more convinced I shouldn't have sold it. {なおさら売るんじゃなかったという気持ちになる}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.13,0:08:13.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's too late now to say your lamentations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.29,0:08:17.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Residing constantly in remorse \Nis not like you at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.39,0:08:19.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I guess you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.39,0:08:34.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it now, Lucy-May?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.57,0:08:37.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Need you to come here for a sec!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.45,0:08:39.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What did you see there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.01,0:08:39.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ants.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.67,0:08:42.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What about the ants?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.16,0:08:44.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There are so many of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.27,0:08:48.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's nothing unusual at all, \Nback in England, there was just as many.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.59,0:08:52.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And they've such an impressive procession! \NLooks like they're carrying something. {line; queue; procession; parade}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.19,0:08:55.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just leave them alone already! \NCome on, we need to go!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.21,0:08:56.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.63,0:09:02.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's sugar! They're carrying sugar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.81,0:09:04.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Stop talking nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.56,0:09:07.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There can't possibly be any sugar around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.08,0:09:08.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.63,0:09:10.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder how far will they go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.70,0:09:22.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, you're right! \NA whole lot of ants. {actually "amazing ants" but I think she means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.09,0:09:24.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And the white thing is the sugar, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.90,0:09:30.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Could as well be salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.48,0:09:32.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ants never carry salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.66,0:09:33.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.53,0:09:44.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Someone must've dropped these here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.35,0:09:47.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's that sack. The ants go in and out \Nthrough where it's torn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.22,0:09:53.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And inside it - sugar?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.67,0:09:54.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sugar.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.50,0:09:55.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna taste it! {strange thing to say but it is what it is}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.84,0:09:57.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Taste it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.03,0:09:59.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We've not tasted any sugar in ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.59,0:10:00.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.73,0:10:09.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch! Eh! An ant just bit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.34,0:10:15.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Sweet! {delicious!}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.01,0:10:19.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.68,0:10:22.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister, this is sugar.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.86,0:10:24.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it belongs to someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.93,0:10:28.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They threw it away! \NYou know, like the goat we've scouted before. {not sure what she means: 捨ててったのよほら前にヤギを拾ったわあたしたち}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.94,0:10:32.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But with this one, someone clearly intended \Nto come pick it up later.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.48,0:10:34.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But by the time they do...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.98,0:10:39.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,the ants will totally end up \Ntaking all of the sugar away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.95,0:10:41.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's yummy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.36,0:10:43.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It is. But the ants are all sour! {/distasteful}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.06,0:10:48.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? Mhm! They're tickling my mouth from inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.67,0:10:52.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My... You two are incorrigible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.00,0:10:54.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sis, you should try it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.59,0:10:55.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.38,0:10:57.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You just need to spit the ants out. {hope i got it right}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.94,0:11:15.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sweet, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.78,0:11:20.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yummy, isn't it, sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.12,0:11:25.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.50,0:11:31.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,One stung me inside my mouth!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.34,0:11:36.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it's still yummy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.81,0:11:52.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Take this! And this! You wretch!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.80,0:11:57.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it all! \NThey dare to make fun of humans!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.39,0:12:01.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Move it! Crap! Wretch! Damn you! {vobsubs have first word as "e-i" but I doubt it}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.01,0:12:06.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, walk! I'm talking to you! \NWalk! Start walking, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.58,0:12:07.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You wretches!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.16,0:12:21.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go first, then, Mr. Pettywell. {actually he means "we're going ahead" informing him that they need to walk past them on a narrow road or something idk}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.72,0:12:23.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.70,0:12:29.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it! Now this riffraff Popple, too! {shithead; bastard​}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.82,0:12:32.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Master, I suggest you stop now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.30,0:12:33.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do what you want!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.60,0:12:43.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,D-D-Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.14,0:12:49.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We should've taken \Nthat sack of sugar with us, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.43,0:12:51.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All better than letting the ants eat it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.41,0:12:55.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we return to take it, sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.68,0:12:57.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But we've walked quite far already.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.38,0:12:59.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now I can't help thinking \Nwe've chosen the wrong road.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.75,0:13:00.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.94,0:13:04.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.62,0:13:08.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Back when we stopped to taste the sugar, \Ndidn't we turn too far to the right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.68,0:13:11.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we should be fine \Nif we turn to the left now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.02,0:13:20.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Will we be all right, sis? {unsure what she means tbh}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.86,0:13:23.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.90,0:13:28.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I really shouldn't have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.67,0:13:44.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister, can't you walk a little slower?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.78,0:13:46.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.63,0:13:49.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I must've been walking \Na bit too fast, haven't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.07,0:13:51.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean we really got off track?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.95,0:13:53.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.43,0:13:57.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But don't you worry. This must be \Nthe direction to Adelaide now, no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.31,0:14:00.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, can you still walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.19,0:14:01.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.28,0:14:08.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.55,0:14:09.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.72,0:14:11.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.32,0:14:14.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's some creature \Nthat's been following us for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.33,0:14:16.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.29,0:14:18.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A person?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.37,0:14:20.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No. An animal, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.48,0:14:22.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, did you notice it, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.45,0:14:23.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No idea what's this about. {hope she means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.71,0:14:26.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure of it! \NCould it be some beast? {beast; brute; animal}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.68,0:14:31.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No scary animals prey around here, \Nso we should be safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.82,0:14:33.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I got a bad feeling!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.97,0:14:36.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, let's keep walking \Nand see how it plays out. {/while observing the situation}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.82,0:14:44.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How about now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.86,0:14:46.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not sure yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.62,0:14:57.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate, maybe it was just your imagination, after all? {lit: there's nothing after all, is there}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.54,0:14:58.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.02,0:14:59.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.93,0:15:01.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.03,0:15:08.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There {\i1}is{\i0} something?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.09,0:15:10.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,See? It was just like I said!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.42,0:15:11.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Could be a dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.53,0:15:12.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,"A dog," you say? {unsure what she means tbh 犬ですって！}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.80,0:15:14.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't it a wolf?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.01,0:15:15.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A wolf, you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.56,0:15:17.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There shouldn't be any wolves around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.93,0:15:19.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.06,0:15:20.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At least, that's what I'm told.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.81,0:15:23.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be aiming to attack us?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.31,0:15:24.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.35,0:15:27.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, let's keep walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.02,0:15:29.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Got it? You two, stick closely to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.07,0:15:31.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'll show our disregard for the beast \Nwith our gait. {あのケダモノを 無視するように歩くのよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.86,0:15:32.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.45,0:15:35.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't break into a run, \Nand match your rhythm with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.29,0:15:42.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,One, two, one, two, one, two.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.22,0:15:47.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,One, two, one, two, one, two.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.55,0:15:48.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.61,0:15:49.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.68,0:15:53.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sis, you're shivering, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.01,0:15:55.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.62,0:15:58.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,One, two, one, two.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.14,0:16:15.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The girls must have already arrived \Nto our new house by now. {/children}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.32,0:16:17.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not so much a house, as a shack. \NIt's a shack, Annie.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.99,0:16:19.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, aren't they the same thing, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.89,0:16:22.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is what we call a shack, \Nnot essentially just a small house?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.47,0:16:24.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that one is especially small and dirty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.29,0:16:29.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope the girls manage to clean it up nicely \Nby the time we get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.38,0:16:33.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it seems, that one shack can't ever become tidy, \Neven after you clean it up. {unsure what he means: それが掃除をすればきれいに なるような小屋じゃないんだよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.90,0:16:38.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, just what kind of shack \Ndid you buy, darling?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.41,0:16:40.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, you'll know when you see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.10,0:16:45.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, if you want to build a picture of it in your head, \Njust think of the most miserable shack that can ever be. {lit: when thoughts come to mind; to have inspiration, as pitiful as possible cabin imagine}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.40,0:16:48.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This way, seeing the real thing \Nis not that disappointing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.00,0:16:50.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,, Is it really that horrible a shack?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.40,0:16:51.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Barely a shelter from the weather. {to protect against the elements; to shelter oneself from the weather}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.44,0:16:57.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which means, the girls are bound to get struck \Nby disappointment, once they arrive to the shack.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.00,0:17:03.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,One, two, one, two, one, two...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.09,0:17:08.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,One, two, one, two.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.84,0:17:10.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's still following us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.34,0:17:12.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! My heart is about to stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.27,0:17:14.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,For some reason, it doesn't seem poised to attack. {何だか襲ってきそうもないようね}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.84,0:17:16.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How could you tell that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.79,0:17:19.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If it wanted to attack, \Nit would've already attacked by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.71,0:17:21.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Should we try to dash?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.06,0:17:22.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To dash?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.12,0:17:23.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's dash!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.39,0:17:25.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know it doesn't \Nspring at us from behind? {emphatically (bite, gulp, chew, etc.)}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.53,0:17:34.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, I can't bear it any longer. \NWe're dashing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.78,0:17:35.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.70,0:17:41.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sis! It's chasing us!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.33,0:17:43.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We can't stop! Keep running!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.63,0:17:58.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.49,0:18:04.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy-May, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.48,0:18:33.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This dog doesn't seem to be the one \Nthat's been chasing us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.21,0:18:34.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.34,0:18:37.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,At least the dog that's been \Nchasing us is gone now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.56,0:18:47.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, Monocle! \NWhat are you barking at so loud? {モノクル - could be monokuru tbh but that sounds way too japanese for 1800 australia}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.15,0:18:52.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now! Monocle!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.60,0:19:00.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you barking like an idiot \Nat a bunch of ladies so lovely?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.70,0:19:05.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I imagine, you girls are coming \Nfrom a place entirely foreign to him. {hope he means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.49,0:19:08.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, are we close to Adelaide already?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.00,0:19:08.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.00,0:19:17.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All the folk coming from the shore always ask me one \Nand the same thing, "are we close to Adelaide already?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.05,0:19:20.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And I always respond, \Nthis here is Adelaide.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.01,0:19:20.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.88,0:19:22.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This here is the city of Adelaide?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.74,0:19:24.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, everyone is surprised at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.38,0:19:28.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And then, you're to ask, \N"but there's not a single house around, is there?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.89,0:19:30.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know what's this about!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.70,0:19:34.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This here is the city park area, \Nthat surrounds Adelaide, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.31,0:19:36.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now that's surprising \Nhow well-informed you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.05,0:19:38.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's thanks to dad telling us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.86,0:19:43.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When he and our brother returned from Adelaide, \Ndad mentioned meeting a shepherd here. {liberal here because lit sounds awful}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.80,0:19:46.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right! It has to be you, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.55,0:19:50.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That might very well be true, I've been telling \Nthis very same thing to a number of folk. {unsure why he says "the same story", like, what story? about adelaide being here}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.09,0:19:54.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, there aren't any roads \Nat where you're coming from.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.02,0:19:56.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We got off track by mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.85,0:19:58.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.09,0:20:01.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But well, at least you didn't end up \Nwalking in circles through the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.81,0:20:02.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.81,0:20:03.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.84,0:20:08.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We were chased all the way until we got to there \Nby some dog-like creature. {wording is a bit awkward but "to there" has to match in time with her pointing finger}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.51,0:20:10.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Some dog-like fellow?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.29,0:20:13.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was mighty scary! Was that a wolf?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.22,0:20:17.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'd wager it was a dingo. \NYou could say that thing is like a feral dog. {wild; growing wild; living in the wild}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.98,0:20:20.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, actually! Was that why you were barking?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.19,0:20:22.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My bad, my bad, Monocle.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.60,0:20:25.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are those dingo things real? {not sure what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.60,0:20:26.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.90,0:20:32.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The aborigines had some luck taming those enough \Nto keep them as pets, but they are still quite ferocious, {unsure what ht means tbh: 原住民の中には うまく手なづけて飼っている者もいるがなかなか凶暴で羊も 時々襲われるんだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.12,0:20:34.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes even attacking the sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.00,0:20:37.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Which means you could keep dingo as a pet, \Nif you feel so inclined? {それじゃあ飼おうと思えば 飼えるのねディンゴを}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.13,0:20:39.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,For me, it's probably out of question.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.67,0:20:42.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But this little lady might just be able to tame it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.09,0:20:44.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can do it, definitely!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.38,0:20:45.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.84,0:20:47.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, I was just joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.71,0:20:51.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Taming a dingo is by all means \Na fool's errand, especially for you. {/for someone like you doing something like ... is totally impossible}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.90,0:20:56.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, we need to get to this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.06,0:21:00.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All I was told is that it's \Nin the vicinity of River Torrens. {unsure what she means tbh なんでもトーレンス川の近くだと教わったんですが}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.08,0:21:01.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm? Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.37,0:21:11.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hope Ben handles it all right, \Nbeing left completely alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.51,0:21:14.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was quite surprised myself, \Nat how responsible he's become. {again, unsure what's this pile of onomatopoeia is all about: あいつがしっかりしてきたのにはほんとにびっくりしたよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.79,0:21:15.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.37,0:21:21.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Back in England, he'd use up every excuse \Njust to avoid helping out in the fields. {I must be really tired but again, I'm not really grasping her whole point: イギリスに いる時は畑仕事だってろくろく手伝おうとしなかった子なのに}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.00,0:21:23.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If me and Ben work in cooperation,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.47,0:21:27.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,we'll certainly be able to build \Na majestic farm here, in Southern Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.12,0:21:42.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, I need to place a sheet \Nover our luggage again, so I'll head there now. {??? okay this is definitely screwed up, I have no idea why he says "sheet is calling again; calling me back" and why choose such complicated way to say it in the first place? それじゃ僕荷物のシートをかけ直してからそちらへ行きます - assumed kakenaosu here is actually "re-cover with sheet"}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.92,0:21:46.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. And I'll be waiting for you, \Nafter I prepare a delicious dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.72,0:22:10.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor. Doctor! Doctor Dayton! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.46,0:22:24.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Who're you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.88,0:22:26.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Son of Mr. Popple, Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.79,0:22:29.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I know, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.16,0:22:32.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Popple who's gone to Adelaide, right? {unsure, maybe he wants to say something else, like ... went to adelaide, you know that?}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.15,0:22:32.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.37,0:22:34.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.90,0:22:40.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, did I catch a cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.69,0:22:45.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not the rightest thing to ask of a kid, \Nbut if you could get me some booze... {guess, now I absolutely have no idea what he means: その子供に頼むこっちゃないが お酒...}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.48,0:22:47.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get off the ship, doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.30,0:22:49.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I got off.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.02,0:22:52.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I needed to examine Mr. Jamling's leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.06,0:22:58.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! That's right! \NI need to get on the ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.69,0:23:02.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor! The ship had already \Nsailed away long ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.39,0:23:03.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.48,0:23:07.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So I...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.99,0:23:11.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So I've been left behind in Australia, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.14,0:23:13.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.70,0:23:27.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And that should be the River Torrens.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.55,0:23:30.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, our house is in that area!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.29,0:23:31.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.39,0:23:37.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, why don't we hurry up \Nto our new home?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.99,0:23:45.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The city of Adelaide, as I saw it for the first time,\Nwas covered in greenery from all directions. {はじめて見たアデレードの町は一面緑に覆われていました - no clue what to make of ichimen here tbh}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.69,0:23:48.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, \Nwe would all be living here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.70,0:23:53.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Adelaide was majorly \Na city yet to be built. {/not to be completed; to be finished; to be ready (e.g. to serve or eat)}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.80,0:24:07.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Upon arriving to Adelaide,\Nour goat fell into the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.55,0:24:10.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just you wait for me! \NI'll save you in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.41,0:24:14.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"Our Small House".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.34,0:24:15.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it.
